cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper proposes a framework for tracking and connecting news articles to Twitter conversations using machine learning. The paper involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and social media analysis, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
